cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about generative adversarial networks (GANs) and their application in generating photo-realistic images. The paper discusses the use of different distance measures for training the generative network and proposes a new model called generative adversarial mapping networks (GAMNs) to improve on the existing generative moment matching network (GMMN). Given that the paper focuses on GANs and image generation, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the theoretical guarantees of the maximum mean discrepancy (MMD) distance metric, which suggests a possible fit with cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a new model that involves an extra network, which could potentially fit with the cs.GR (Graphics) sub-category.
